1326:				;
1327:				; ASCII to ZX81 key code table. These are the values returned by the ZX81 ROM
1328:				; KEYBOARD routine and turned to character codes by DECODE. They are also
1329:				; stored in LAST_K. Codes 0x20 to 0x7f are included. Codes with no reasonable
1330:				; representation are flagged with 0xf fff (no key pressed). The ZX81 uses shift
1331:				; space and shift newline, which are problematic for a terminal. For this
1332:				; reason, these are represented as follows:
1333:				; "#" - shift newline ("function")
1334:				; "/" - shift space ("£")
1335:				; Note: newline is 0xfdbf, which is not represented in this table. In addition,
1336:				; shift 3 ("£") sends 0xa3 and should result in a code of 0xf6f7.
